A 67-year-old woman, Beatrice Ogunyemi, is in urgent need of N4 million for brain surgery. Her illness which began in December last year prompted a scan that revealed brain damage. The result of the scan and doctor’s report from Foremost Radiology Consultants Limited was sighted by The Nation. According to her daughter, Ms Esther Ogunyemi, her bedridden mother can hardly recognise people and respond to those around her.   Bandits attack another Niger community     Police arrest ex-staff of Owerri FMC over attempted ‘ritual…     Let’s save Okikiola Abdulahi, girl without anus   The surgery is meant to prevent life-threatening complications and improve her condition. Thus, she is appealing to well-meaning Nigerians for financial assistance towards the surgery. - Advertisement - “We need the assistance of well-meaning citizens of the country to save our mother. She is in critical condition. The doctor said she had an internal brain injury when she fell. We need N4 million to make her return to her normal healthy state,” she said.  Donations can be sent to Stanbic IBTC Bank account 0032915647 Ogunyemi Esther. She can also be reached on 08082963281.